<li><em><strong>Transitioning</strong></em> - Transitioning is the process by which some trans people bring their physical traits and gender expression into alignment with their gender identity. Not all transgender people choose to transition; this is a deeply personal choice. Some trans people who physically transition to the opposite sex identify as <em>transsexual</em>, but this term should be used with caution, since the details of transition are personal and private. When in doubt, just call someone <em>trans</em>.</li>
